e.g. } 4.dxe4 Qxd1+ 5.Nxd1 Nf6 6.f3 e5 7.Ne3 Nfd7 8.Bd2 $14 )
4.d4 $5
( 4.Nf3 { is natural, when } 4...Nf6 $5 { is an intriguing shot at taking over
the initiative - } 5.exd5 cxd5 6.Nxe5
( 6.d4 e4 7.Ne5 Bb4 $15 )
6...d4 7.Qe2 Be7 8.Ne4 Nxe4 9.Qxe4 O-O $36 )
4...dxe4 5.Nxe4 Qxd4 { is already containing a pawn sacrifice by White: } 6.Bd3
( 6.Qxd4 exd4 7.Nf3 Bf5
( 7...c5 8.Bc4 Be6 9.Bxe6 fxe6 10.Bf4 Nf6 11.Neg5 Nc6 $11 )
