11...O-O 12.Nh4 Kh8 13.Qh5 Be6 $15 )
8...exf4 $5 { The same concrete approach for provoking weaknesses. }
( 8...Nge7 9.Bg2 Qc7 $5 { is also possible, then White can close the center by
means of } 10.f5 f6 11.c4 $13 { , which might not be everyone's cup of tea } )
9.gxf4 Qc7 10.e5 Be7 11.Nf2 Nh6 { with decent chances after } 12.Bg2 Nf5 13.Ne4
O-O 14.O-O a5 $1 $15 [%cal Ga8a6,Ga6g6] )
3...dxe4 $5 { seems to be in the spirit of Caro-Kann more than any other
continuation. }
